[370.939632, "o", "He didn't say any more, but we've always been unusually communicative in a reserved way, and I understood that he meant a great deal more than that. In consequence, I'm inclined to reserve all judgments, a habit that has opened up many odd natures to me and also made me the victim of not a few dated bores. The unusual mind is quick to detect and attach itself to this quality when it appears in a normal person, and so it came about that in school I was unjustly accused of being a politician, because I was privy to the secret griefs of wild, unknown men. Most of the confidences were unsought---frequently I have feigned sleep, preoccupation, or a hostile levity when I realized by some unmistakable sign that an close revelation was quivering on the horizon; for the close revelations of new men, or at least the terms in which they express them, are usually copied and marred by obvious suppressions. Reserving judgments is a matter of endless hope. I am still a little afraid of missing something if I forget that, as my father snobbishly suggested, and I snobbishly repeat, a sense of the basic manners is parcelled out unequally at birth.\r\n\r\n"]
[370.940426, "o", "\u001b[?2004hroot@bc17e3cbd220:/app# "]
[383.205944, "i", "cat > check_more.py << 'EOF'\nimport re\n\n# Read synonyms and find shortest option for each word\nsynonym_map = {}\nwith open('synonyms.txt', 'r') as f:\n    for line in f:\n        words = [w.strip() for w in line.strip().split(',')]\n        shortest = min(words, key=len)\n        for word in words:\n            synonym_map[word.lower()] = shortest.lower()\n\nwords_to_check = ['unusually', 'communicative', 'reserved', 'judgments', 'habit',\n                  'natures', 'victim', 'quality', 'normal', 'unknown', 'hostile',\n                  'levity', 'sign', 'revelation', 'revelations', 'terms', 'obvious',\n                  'suppressions', 'hope', 'unsought']\n\nprint(\"Additional words that can be shortened:\")\nfor word in words_to_check:\n    if word.lower() in synonym_map:\n        shortest = synonym_map[word.lower()]\n        if len(shortest) < len(word):\n            print(f\"{word} ({len(word)}) -> {shortest} ({len(shortest)}) saves {len(word)-len(shortest)}\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"{word} ({len(word)}) -> {shortest} ({len(shortest)}) [same or longer]\")\n\nEOF\n"]
[383.20647, "o", "cat > check_more.py << 'EOF'\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
