[493.230065, "i", "head -20 input.tex | grep -E '(odd|dated|unusual|school|close|copied|endless|basic|manners|bogs|focus|always|set|winning|lovely|enhanced|vows|complex|devices|mood|amazing|dreamy|hopes|failed|joys|reaction|wild|trips|scout|worn|useful|land|kind|new|study|home|open|quiet|opinions|prey|trait|jest|exposure|exposures|clear|censorings)'\n"]
[493.233113, "o", "head -20 input.tex | grep -E '(odd|dated|unusual|school|close|copied|endless|basic|manners|bogs|focus|always|set|winning|lovely|enhanced|vows|complex|devices|mood|amazing|dreamy|hopes|failed|joys|reaction|wild|trips|scout|worn|useful|land|kind|new|study|home|open|quiet|opinions|prey|trait|jest|exposure|exposures|clear|censorings)'\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[493.237933, "o", "He didn't say any more, but we've \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kalways\u001b[m\u001b[K been \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kunusual\u001b[m\u001b[Kly \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kopen\u001b[m\u001b[K in a \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kquiet\u001b[m\u001b[K way, and I understood that he meant a great deal more than that. In consequence, I'm inclined to reserve all \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kopinions\u001b[m\u001b[K, a habit that has \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kopen\u001b[m\u001b[Ked up many \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kodd\u001b[m\u001b[K natures to me and also made me the \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kprey\u001b[m\u001b[K of not a few \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kdated\u001b[m\u001b[K bores. The \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kunusual\u001b[m\u001b[K mind is quick to detect and attach itself to this \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Ktrait\u001b[m\u001b[K when it appears in a normal person, and so it came about that in \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kschool\u001b[m\u001b[K I was unjustly accused of being a politician, because I was privy to the secret griefs of \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kwild\u001b[m\u001b[K, unknown men. Most of the confidences were unsought---frequently I have feigned sleep, preoccupation, or a hostile \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kjest\u001b[m\u001b[K when I realized by some unmistakable sign that an \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kclose\u001b[m\u001b[K \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kexposure\u001b[m\u001b[K was quivering on the horizon; for the \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kclose\u001b[m\u001b[K \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kexposures\u001b[m\u001b[K of \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Knew\u001b[m\u001b[K men, or at least the terms in which they express them, are usually \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kcopied\u001b[m\u001b[K and marred by \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kclear\u001b[m\u001b[K \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kcensorings\u001b[m\u001b[K. Reserving \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kopinions\u001b[m\u001b[K is a matter of \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kendless\u001b[m\u001b[K hope. I am still a little afraid of missing something if I forget that, as my father snobbishly suggested, and I snobbishly repeat, a sense of the \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kbasic\u001b[m\u001b[K \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kmanners\u001b[m\u001b[K is parcelled out unequally at birth.\r\n"]
[493.238313, "o", "And, after boasting this way of my tolerance, I come to the admission that it has a limit. Conduct may be founded on the hard rock or the wet \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kbogs\u001b[m\u001b[K, but after a certain point I don't care what it's founded on. When I came back from the East last autumn I felt that I wanted the world to be in uniform and at a sort of moral \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kfocus\u001b[m\u001b[K \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kalways\u001b[m\u001b[K; I wanted no more \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kwild\u001b[m\u001b[K \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Ktrips\u001b[m\u001b[K with privileged glimpses into the human heart. Only Gatsby, the man who gives his name to this book, was exempt from my \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kreaction\u001b[m\u001b[K---Gatsby, who represented everything for which I have an unaffected scorn. If personality is an unbroken \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kset\u001b[m\u001b[K of \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kwinning\u001b[m\u001b[K gestures, then there was something \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Klovely\u001b[m\u001b[K about him, some \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kenhanced\u001b[m\u001b[K sensitivity to the \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kvows\u001b[m\u001b[K of life, as if he were related to one of those \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kcomplex\u001b[m\u001b[K \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kdevices\u001b[m\u001b[K that register earthquakes ten thous"]
[493.238545, "o", "and miles away. This \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kreaction\u001b[m\u001b[K had nothing to do with that flabby impressionability which is dignified under the name of the ``creative \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kmood\u001b[m\u001b[K''---it was an \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kamazing\u001b[m\u001b[K gift for hope, a \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kdreamy\u001b[m\u001b[K readiness such as I have never found in any other person and which it is not likely I shall ever find again. No---Gatsby turned out all right at the end; it is what \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kprey\u001b[m\u001b[Ked on Gatsby, what foul dust floated in the wake of his \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Khopes\u001b[m\u001b[K that temporarily \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kclose\u001b[m\u001b[Kd out my interest in the \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kfailed\u001b[m\u001b[K sorrows and short-winded \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kjoys\u001b[m\u001b[K of men.\r\n"]
[493.238994, "o", "I never saw this great-uncle, but I'm supposed to look like him---with special reference to the rather hard-boiled painting that hangs in father's \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kstudy\u001b[m\u001b[K. I graduated from New Haven in 1915, just a quarter of a century after my father, and a little later I participated in that delayed Teutonic migration known as the Great War. I enjoyed the counter-raid so thoroughly that I came back restless. Instead of being the warm centre of the world, the Middle West now seemed like the ragged edge of the universe---so I decided to go East and learn the bond business. Everybody I k\u001b[01;31m\u001b[Knew\u001b[m\u001b[K was in the bond business, so I supposed it could support one more single man. All my aunts and uncles talked it over as if they were choosing a prep \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kschool\u001b[m\u001b[K for me, and finally said, ``Why---ye-es,'' with very grave, hesitant faces. Father agreed to finance me for a year, and after various delays I came East, permanently, I thought, in the spring of twenty-two.\r\n"]
[493.239286, "o", "The \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kuseful\u001b[m\u001b[K thing was to find rooms in the city, but it was a warm season, and I had just left a \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kland\u001b[m\u001b[K of wide lawns and \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kkind\u001b[m\u001b[K trees, so when a \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Knew\u001b[m\u001b[K man at the \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kstudy\u001b[m\u001b[K suggested that we take a \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Khome\u001b[m\u001b[K together in a commuting town, it sounded like a great idea. He found the \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Khome\u001b[m\u001b[K, a \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kworn\u001b[m\u001b[K cardboard bungalow at eighty a month, but at the last minute the firm ordered him to Washington, and I went out to the \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kland\u001b[m\u001b[K alone. I had a dog---at least I had him for a few days until he ran away---and an old Dodge and a Finnish woman, who made my bed and cooked breakfast and muttered Finnish wisdom to herself over the electric stove.\r\nI told him. And as I walked on I was lonely no longer. I was a guide, a \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kscout\u001b[m\u001b[K, an original \u001b[01;31m\u001b[Kset\u001b[m\u001b[Ktler. He had casually conferred on me the freedom of the neighborhood.\r\n"]
